I'm very glad that I enrolled. I've already learned so much about Solana development, and I'm finally starting to understand what people mean when they talk about technologies like Web3/dapp etc. 

It's also useful that you learn a variety of ways to develop. You can develop from scratch, or with Rust, or with the terminal, or with JavaScript, or with certain Solana libraries like Metaplex, and Arjun covers all these different techniques in the course so you have a toolkit.

I'm hoping to pick up a blockchain developer gig in either Eithereum or Solana, and I'm thankful this course has given me the knowledge I need for Solana.

This was a really good course! Arjun is incredibly proficient in his work, and when queried in the questions he provides meaningful answers. 

The course is short, so it speeds through concepts quite quickly. This course is an implementation guide and does not stress the theory of either Rust or Solana. This is good in many ways as it gets to the point. Those looking for a deeper dive into Rust should do a Rust-specific course. Very happy overall.
